cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with a communication problem involving channels and sources, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of a relay and the consideration of multiple users also suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of correlations among sources, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of functional-decode-forward channel coding suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the study of achievable rates could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
